    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)

        vmax = max(args)

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)
        """
        error = kwargs['error'] if 'error' in kwargs else 0.16
        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)
        error_message = '' if 'error_message' not in kwargs else kwargs['error_message']

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)
        """
        error = kwargs['error'] if 'error' in kwargs else 0.16
        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)
        error_message = '' if 'error_message' not in kwargs else kwargs['error_message']

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)

        vmin = min(args)

        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check

        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)
        """
        error = kwargs['error'] if 'error' in kwargs else 0.16
        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)
        error_message = '' if 'error_message' not in kwargs else kwargs['error_message']
        assert vmin > vmax * (1.0 - error) or vmin == vmax, \
>           "values not within {:.2f}% of the max: {} ({})".format(error * 100, args, error_message)

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)

        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)
        """
        error = kwargs['error'] if 'error' in kwargs else 0.16
        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)
        error_message = '' if 'error_message' not in kwargs else kwargs['error_message']
        assert vmin > vmax * (1.0 - error) or vmin == vmax, \
>           "values not within {:.2f}% of the max: {} ({})".format(error * 100, args, error_message)

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)
        """
        error = kwargs['error'] if 'error' in kwargs else 0.16
        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)
        error_message = '' if 'error_message' not in kwargs else kwargs['error_message']

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)
        """

        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)
        """
        error = kwargs['error'] if 'error' in kwargs else 0.16
        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)
        error_message = '' if 'error_message' not in kwargs else kwargs['error_message']

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)
        """

        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)

        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:

        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)
        """
        error = kwargs['error'] if 'error' in kwargs else 0.16
        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)
        error_message = '' if 'error_message' not in kwargs else kwargs['error_message']
        assert vmin > vmax * (1.0 - error) or vmin == vmax, \
>           "values not within {:.2f}% of the max: {} ({})".format(error * 100, args, error_message)
E       AssertionError: values not within 10.00% of the max: (3098875, 1330245, 2833670) (node5)

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)

        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)
        """
        error = kwargs['error'] if 'error' in kwargs else 0.16
        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)
        error_message = '' if 'error_message' not in kwargs else kwargs['error_message']

    def assert_almost_equal(*args, **kwargs):
        """
        Assert variable number of arguments all fall within a margin of error.
        @params *args variable number of numerical arguments to check
        @params error Optional margin of error. Default 0.16
        @params error_message Optional error message to print. Default ''
    
        Examples:
        assert_almost_equal(sizes[2], init_size)
        assert_almost_equal(ttl_session1, ttl_session2[0][0], error=0.005)
        """

        vmax = max(args)
        vmin = min(args)
        error_message = '' if 'error_message' not in kwargs else kwargs['error_message']
